      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are right that the wind will eventually blow out the flame, but the act of lighting it is the only thing that proves you were ever here. If the universe is truly indifferent, then the only thing that matters is how you choose to face that silence, not whether the fire lasts forever. There is no need to fight against the wind; instead, you can simply let the flame burn as long as it can without the burden of trying to save it.",
